1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
Are you guys ready to get this party started?!

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:04,240
Yeah!

3
00:00:04,240 --> 00:00:06,200
You're as popular as ever.

4
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:09,200
And you're as gloomy as ever.

5
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:11,200
Alright then.

6
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,240
Let's decide on our events for the Sports Festival!

7
00:00:13,240 --> 00:00:13,880
I've got one! I've got one!

8
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:14,480
Go ahead.

9
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:15,840
Iijima Hinata, you should do the scavenger hunt.

10
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:17,560
And make sure you come find me for your item.

11
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,000
Stop trying to make it all about you!

12
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:19,840
What's the harm in that?

13
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:20,760
Come find me instead!

14
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:22,080
No, you should come find me!

15
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:23,080
No, pick me! Pick me!

16
00:00:23,080 --> 00:00:24,560
Alright, alright, I get it.

17
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:26,400
But more importantly, I want to settle this first.

18
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:29,040
The relay race team members!

19
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:30,280
Oh yeah!

20
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,880
This is the main stage for us men!

21
00:00:32,880 --> 00:00:35,320
Time to show off our sweat and tears!

22
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:37,360
If I don't run, who will?

23
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:40,920
So then.

24
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:42,520
Raise your hand if you can run 50 meters in under seven seconds.

25
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,160
Just one?

26
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,200
What about Kono Mizuki?

27
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,600
Mizuki?

28
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Mizuki!

29
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:56,160
Back in middle school,

30
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:58,000
weren't you unbeatable in the class relay?

31
00:00:58,480 --> 00:00:59,520
That was back then...

32
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:00,360
That's insane!

33
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:01,800
It'd be a waste if you didn't run!

34
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:04,160
Huh, that's a surprise.

35
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:05,640
Alright, it's settled!

36
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:08,000
We still need two more people.

37
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,240
Two more, huh?

38
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:10,840
Oh, what about Iijima Hinata?

39
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:14,920
I can't yet.

40
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:18,000
I see... take care of yourself.

41
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:19,640
Wait, wait, wait.

42
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:23,400
I heard his injury from the track team hasn't fully healed yet.

43
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:24,280
Wait, really?

44
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:26,320
Then he can't participate in the race either...

45
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,400
There's so much about you

46
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,920
that I don't know.
